description.narrative:
Assistance is provided in line with cluster (WASH, Shelter & NFI) standards and beneficiaries are selected based upon agreed vulnerability criteria:
-	Female Headed Household; 
-	Child Headed Household; 
-	Disabled Headed Household; 
-	Elderly Headed Household with no adults having an income; 
-	Households with children under 5 with Severe Acute Malnutrition (SAM) or Moderate Acute Malnutrition (MAM);
-	Vulnerable Households with children under five years old and/or pregnant women and/or lactating women;
-	Very Large Family (8 members or more) with only one adult having an income; 
-	Very Poor Families; 
-	Families with Chronically-ill or disabled members or having other pressing vulnerability.
